<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - REASSEMBLY - REMOTE CONTROL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="29">
        <title>REMOTE CONTROL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean the remote housing, making sure it is free from burrs
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c8">(Figure 128</hotlnk>). Place it on a work bench.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022c8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022c8" filename="../figg13/g13022c8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 128. Remote Control Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the idler finger bore with Lubriplate grease. Place the idler finger over the
                shift finger, with the two fingers close together (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022c9">Figure 129</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022c9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022c9" filename="../figg13/g13022c9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 129. Idler Finger &#38; Shift Finger</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the fingers with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d0">Figure 130</hotlnk>). The rolled die side of the ring should be toward the
                idler finger.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d0" filename="../figg13/g13022d0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 130. Secured With Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new O-ring over the shift shaft if one hasn't been installed already (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d1">Figure 131</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d1" filename="../figg13/g13022d1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 131. O-Ring Placement</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Avoid cutting the O-ring by using a screwdriver to hold it away from the keyway during
                    installation.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the shift shaft with Lubriplate grease. Align the shift fingers with the housing
                bore, and insert the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d2">Figure 132</hotlnk>). It should slide easily through the assembly; do not
                force it. The shaft keyway must align with the shift finger key.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d2" filename="../figg13/g13022d2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 132. Shift Finger Alignment</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place new O-rings on the shift pistons (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d3">Figure 133</hotlnk>). Lubricate the O-rings and housing bore with Lubriplate
                or a comparable high quality lubricant.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d3" filename="../figg13/g13022d3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 133. Shift Pistons</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the joiner pin in one of the pistons, using Lubriplate grease to hold it in position
                for assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d4">Figure 134</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d4" filename="../figg13/g13022d4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 134. Joiner Pin</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the shift pistons in the housing, one from each side (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d5">Figure 135</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d5" filename="../figg13/g13022d5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 135. Shift Pins In Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not push the pistons all the way through the housing from the side; it may cause the pistons to
                    bind.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new O-rings on the housing plugs. Apply Lubriplate or the equivalent. Install the
                plugs into the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d6">Figure 136</hotlnk>). Tighten them to 80 ft-lbs. (108 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d6" filename="../figg13/g13022d6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 136. New O-Rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the control arm subassembly to the end of the shift shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d7">Figure 137</hotlnk>). Secure with washer and bolt. Tighten the bolt to 10
                ft-lbs. (14 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d7" filename="../figg13/g13022d7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 137. Control Arm Subassembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Hold the fingers still to prevent the assembly from hitting the housing and becoming damaged
                    during tightening.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the breather was removed during disassembly, replace it now (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d8">Figure 138</hotlnk>). Place a new O-ring on the automatic switch and apply
                Lubriplate or the equivalent. Install it and tighten to 14 ft-lbs. (19 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d8" filename="../figg13/g13022d8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 138. Replace Breather</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat the actuator cover mounting surface with purple Loctite 515 or the equivalent. Install
                it (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022d9">Figure 139</hotlnk>). Secure with four bolts tightened to 32 ft-lbs. (43 N&#183;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022d9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022d9" filename="../figg13/g13022d9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 139. Actuator Cover Mounting Surface</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pack the remote shift rod housing with Lubriplate grease or the equivalent (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e0">Figure 140</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e0" filename="../figg13/g13022e0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 140. Shift Rod Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the shift rod with Lubriplate grease or the equivalent and slide it into the
                housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e1">Figure 141</hotlnk>). Install the finger on the shaft and secure it with a set
                screw. Tighten to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54 to 68 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e1" filename="../figg13/g13022e1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 141. Install Finger On Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the seal over the shift rod into the housing bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e2">Figure 142</hotlnk>). The cupped side of the seal goes into the bore first.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e2" filename="../figg13/g13022e2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 142. Seal Over Shift Rod</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the boot (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e3">Figure 143</hotlnk>). Secure it with a tie-down strap.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e3" filename="../figg13/g13022e3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 143. Install Boot</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the outer shift control lever, aligning it with the inner shift finger (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e4">Figure 144</hotlnk>). Secure it with a bolt. Tighten to 40 to 50 ft-lbs. (54
                to 68 N&#183;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e4" filename="../figg13/g13022e4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 144. Outer Shift Control Lever</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the selection lever (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e5">Figure 145</hotlnk>). Secure it with a washer and bolt. Tighten to 40 to 50
                ft-lbs. (54 to 68 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e5" filename="../figg13/g13022e5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 145. Install Selection Lever</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place thread sealer on the tie rod bolt (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e6">Figure 146</hotlnk>). Install the tie rod assembly. Tighten to 60 to 80
                ft-lbs. (81 to 108 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e6" filename="../figg13/g13022e6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 146. Tie Rod Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the other end of the tie rod assembly with the castellated nut and cotter pin (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e7">Figure 147</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e7" filename="../figg13/g13022e7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 147. Secure Other End of Tie Rod</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lightly coat the rack bore with Lubriplate or a comparable high quality lubricant that won't
                attack seals or metal parts. Place the shift rack into the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e8">Figure 148</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e8" filename="../figg13/g13022e8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 148. Lubricate Rack Bore</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The lever slot must face up and the cut out portion must be seen through the housing for proper
                    operation.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place two new O-rings on each inner piston and one new O-ring on each outer piston (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022e9">Figure 149</hotlnk>). Apply Lubriplate or a comparable high quality lubricant.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022e9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022e9" filename="../figg13/g13022e9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 149. O-Rings On Each Inner Piston</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the pistons into the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022f0">Figure 150</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022f0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022f0" filename="../figg13/g13022f0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 150. Pistons Into Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the end caps and gaskets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022f1">Figure 151</hotlnk>). Tighten the bolts to 20 ft-lbs. (27 N&#183; m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022f1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022f1" filename="../figg13/g13022f1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 151. End Caps &#38; Gaskets</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place new O-rings on the override plunger and cap (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022f2">Figure 152</hotlnk>). Apply Lubriplate or the equivalent. Then install the
                plunger and cap. Tighten the cap to 45 ft-lbs. (61 N&#183; m). Secure it with the hitch pin.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022f2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022f2" filename="../figg13/g13022f2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 152. Plunger &#38; Cap</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two new O-rings in each valve port (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022f3">Figure 153</hotlnk>). Lubricate them with Lubriplate or the equivalent.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022f3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022f3" filename="../figg13/g13022f3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 153. Lubricate O-Rings In Valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the valves in their proper location-"HI," "N" and "LOW" (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022f4">Figure 154</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022f4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022f4" filename="../figg13/g13022f4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 154. Valves In Location</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the tube assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022f5">Figure 155</hotlnk>). Hold the valves steady with a wrench while you tighten
                the fitting nuts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022f5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022f5" filename="../figg13/g13022f5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 155. Install Tube Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the shift shaft with Moly grease. Coat the actuator assembly (right,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022f6">Figure 156</hotlnk>) with Loctite 515 or the equivalent. Place the actuator
                assembly over the lever.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022f6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022f6" filename="../figg13/g13022f6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 156. Actuator Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The control arm must be aligned with the sensor in neutral position to ensure proper operation.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure it with four bolts. Tighten bolts to 34 ft-lbs. (46 N&#183; m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the shield. Secure with bolts and tighten to 20 ft-lbs. (27 N&#183; m). Re-attach
                the wire harnesses. Place a gasket on the main case and install the remote control assembly. Secure with
                bolts tightened to 31 to 45 ft-lbs. (42 to 61 N&#183; m). Attach the spear rod once the unit is
                re-installed into the vehicle.
            </para>
        </step1>
